Flames shot from Thassalin's maw as the huge Thraki set a specific piece of forest in Band and then circled overhead to detect movements. Strange enough, the eerie screeching behind him faded as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's going on, Tenuk, you already turned yourself into a Thraki once!"
"Flying on my own is completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in Nyssi's opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. Thassalin apparently didn't mind. Nevertheless, he had realized that he had scared his new friends, and landed on a clearing.
"I'm sorry, but I smelled something. I had to take care of it!"
"But did you have to drag us along?" growled Tenuk as he climbed down from Thassalin's back and slid down onto his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter! How is he supposed to catch up with us?"
"He'll think of something..." growled Nyssi. "Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not stupid."
"Yes, but can Retvik drive?"
Nyssi winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice little car like Kayel's either. Plus, he only started using the car for work because you always drive us. He only has a bicycle."
Laughter rang out, interrupting them. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something incredibly funny, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took a little too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'm sorry, but I imagined your huge friend in armor on such a tiny little bicycle for Temthan children. That was hilarious! I wish I had some kind of telepathy. A beautiful image! One I can't share!"
Kayel chuckled, as he could imagine what was going on in Thassalin's mind. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, took off, and disappeared. When he returned after a short time, he threw something lifeless at Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, silver-white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "Another dead one. I hear their screams. I smell their blood. Something is urging me to protect and hunt. As Yisini commands. They are very close."
The mighty Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and watched intently at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and snarled. Whatever it was, it spread two huge wing pairs and shot toward Thassalin, without paying any attention to the three smaller creatures between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely get into cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and hurling him with his incredibly long, skillful tail onto his back, before he himself took to the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel snapped angrily while he took his rifle off his back and opened a bag containing a ammunition belt. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you turn into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"Do you want to follow them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a huge monster!"
"And so what? I'm standing here with a high-quality rifle in my hand and could shoot immediately. But, well, how should I put it – I would have to see it first in order to hit it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make more room. With a quiet, painful grunt, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned into scales and his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light-blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Like an ordinary Thraki, Tenuk now had a proper scale shield running along his back. Practically, he also had a pair of spines on his back, on which Kayel could hold on. It took a little too long for Tenuk to get the flight started, but once in the air, he oriented himself quickly and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid a collision.
"Is that the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too focused on the flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other beast was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in sight. The fact that it was pursuing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It roared in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it would certainly not be able to keep up with them.
A ways ahead, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin swung around and spat fire at the darkened monster. The creature was definitely injured. It seemed furious, but not willing to give up. The fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old-fashioned shot gun. It was not necessarily the first choice, but maybe the shot would scare off the black beast.
